# Project-specific: large data and trained weights do not belong in git.
# `results/<date>-<slice>-<short-description>/` is project-tracked (the four
# text files config.yaml, git_hash.txt, metrics.json, notes.md per
# `docs/07-experiment-scaffold.md`); the rules below keep large artefacts out.
data/
*.pth
*.ckpt
*.pt
wandb/

# George's KICS paper artefacts (personal academic output, not project-tracked).
# The slice's engineering work — code, tests, results dirs, figure scripts,
# and the status pointer at `papers/team/george-kics-status.md` — stays
# tracked. The paper itself (`.tex/.pdf/.bib/figures/`) lives only locally.
papers/kics-george/
